stylometry: Decision Trees or important in problem solving beacuse they allow us to see which strategies should be used to reach a certain goal.  Decision Trees do not just show the results of a particular problem, they show the full decision making process through steps. A Decision Tree can be used when deciding between two jobs. The options can be Job A, Job B, or neither, by analyzing the amount of money made, the amount of benifits given, the cost of living, and the initial cost of moving. Although the decision tree may not take into effect the emotional effects of which job chosen, it can describe which job would be best money wise.
